FROM jsonb_to_recordset('[{"id": "cap-114-english-reading-015", "exam_id": "cap", "subject_id": "sub-cap-english-reading", "paper_id": "cap-114-english-reading", "question_type": "single_choice", "question_text": "machines have been used to pick fruits for a long time, they were not used on\nstrawberry farms until several years ago.", "options": ["Although", "Because", "Before", "If"], "correct_answer": 0, "correct_answer_json": null, "parent_question_id": null, "media": null, "source": "official", "source_meta": {"parser_version": "cap_v0.1", "merger_version": "cap_merger_v0.2", "parsed_at": "2026-04-25T18:39:39+00:00", "source_pdf_sha1": "dec9486b85ec", "answer_pdf_sha1": "6a98d676c5b0", "flags": [], "parse_confidence": 1.0, "original_question_number": 15, "raw_text": "15.\t        machines have been used to pick fruits for a long time, they were not used on\n    strawberry farms until several years ago.\n    (A) Although          (B) Because          (C) Before              (D) If\n", "explanation_source": "ai_v1_inline"}, "is_active": true, "auto_gradable": true, "difficulty": 3, "explanation": "前後子句語意對立（採收水果的機器使用已久 vs. 草莓農場才剛開始用），需轉折連接詞，故 (A) Although 正確。(B) Because、(C) Before、(D) If 皆不適合表達讓步轉折。"}, {"id": "cap-114-english-reading-016", "exam_id": "cap", "subject_id": "sub-cap-english-reading", "paper_id": "cap-114-english-reading", "question_type": "single_choice", "question_text": "There are online videos that teach you exercises you can do at home.  They’ll            you a\ntrip to the gym, and some money too.", "options": ["cost", "give", "keep", "save"], "correct_answer": 3, "correct_answer_json": null, "parent_question_id": null, "media": null, "source": "official", "source_meta": {"parser_version": "cap_v0.1", "merger_version": "cap_merger_v0.2", "parsed_at": "2026-04-25T18:39:39+00:00", "source_pdf_sha1": "dec9486b85ec", "answer_pdf_sha1": "6a98d676c5b0", "flags": [], "parse_confidence": 1.0, "original_question_number": 16, "raw_text": "16. There are online videos that teach you exercises you can do at home.  They’ll            you a\n    trip to the gym, and some money too.\n    (A) cost               (B) give              (C) keep             (D) save\n", "explanation_source": "ai_v1_inline"}, "is_active": true, "auto_gradable": true, "difficulty": 3, "explanation": "「線上運動影片可省去你上健身房的行程，也省下一些錢」，「save you a trip + save money」是固定用法，故 (D) save 正確。(A) cost 是花費；(B) give、(C) keep 與省去成本的語意不合。"}, {"id": "cap-114-english-reading-017", "exam_id": "cap", "subject_id": "sub-cap-english-reading", "paper_id": "cap-114-english-reading", "question_type": "single_choice", "question_text": "Jane’s parents are always happy to see their grandchildren, but mine        less so when I\nvisit them with my kids.", "options": ["is", "are", "do", "does"], "correct_answer": 1, "correct_answer_json": null, "parent_question_id": null, "media": null, "source": "official", "source_meta": {"parser_version": "cap_v0.1", "merger_version": "cap_merger_v0.2", "parsed_at": "2026-04-25T18:39:39+00:00", "source_pdf_sha1": "dec9486b85ec", "answer_pdf_sha1": "6a98d676c5b0", "flags": [], "parse_confidence": 1.0, "original_question_number": 17, "raw_text": "17.   Jane’s parents are always happy to see their grandchildren, but mine        less so when I\n      visit them with my kids.\n      (A) is                 (B) are                (C) do               (D) does\n", "explanation_source": "ai_v1_inline"}, "is_active": true, "auto_gradable": true, "difficulty": 3, "explanation": "主詞 mine（= my parents）為複數，故動詞用 are，回應前句「are always happy」的對應結構，故 (B) are 正確。(A) is 為單數；(C) do、(D) does 不適合形容詞 less so 的補語。"}, {"id": "cap-114-english-reading-018", "exam_id": "cap", "subject_id": "sub-cap-english-reading", "paper_id": "cap-114-english-reading", "question_type": "single_choice", "question_text": "Before she           about it, you should tell Daphne you broke her favorite cup.", "options": ["asks", "asked", "was asking", "will ask"], "correct_answer": 0, "correct_answer_json": null, "parent_question_id": null, "media": null, "source": "official", "source_meta": {"parser_version": "cap_v0.1", "merger_version": "cap_merger_v0.2", "parsed_at": "2026-04-25T18:39:39+00:00", "source_pdf_sha1": "dec9486b85ec", "answer_pdf_sha1": "6a98d676c5b0", "flags": [], "parse_confidence": 1.0, "original_question_number": 18, "raw_text": "18. Before she           about it, you should tell Daphne you broke her favorite cup.\n    (A) asks                (B) asked               (C) was asking        (D) will ask\n", "explanation_source": "ai_v1_inline"}, "is_active": true, "auto_gradable": true, "difficulty": 3, "explanation": "副詞子句 before 的時間從句，當主句使用未來語意（you should tell）時，從句用一般現在式表示未來，故 (A) asks 正確。(B) asked 為過去式；(C) was asking 為過去進行式；(D) will ask 在 before 子句中不能用未來式。"}, {"id": "cap-114-english-reading-019", "exam_id": "cap", "subject_id": "sub-cap-english-reading", "paper_id": "cap-114-english-reading", "question_type": "single_choice", "question_text": "It was very windy this morning.   Some of the shirts on the balcony were blown away\nin the pond.", "options": ["fell", "and fell", "fallen", "and fallen"], "correct_answer": 1, "correct_answer_json": null, "parent_question_id": null, "media": null, "source": "official", "source_meta": {"parser_version": "cap_v0.1", "merger_version": "cap_merger_v0.2", "parsed_at": "2026-04-25T18:39:39+00:00", "source_pdf_sha1": "dec9486b85ec", "answer_pdf_sha1": "6a98d676c5b0", "flags": [], "parse_confidence": 1.0, "original_question_number": 19, "raw_text": "19. It was very windy this morning.   Some of the shirts on the balcony were blown away\n             in the pond.\n    (A) fell              (B) and fell       (C) fallen            (D) and fallen\n\n\n\n\n", "explanation_source": "ai_v1_inline"}, "is_active": true, "auto_gradable": true, "difficulty": 3, "explanation": "前句主動語態「Some of the shirts...were blown away」，後句以對等連接詞並列同主詞動詞，需「and fell」連接過去式動詞，故 (B) and fell 正確。(A) fell 缺連接詞；(C)(D) 形式不正確。"}, {"id": "cap-114-english-reading-020", "exam_id": "cap", "subject_id": "sub-cap-english-reading", "paper_id": "cap-114-english-reading", "question_type": "single_choice", "question_text": "What happened to Rex?", "options": ["He got lost.", "He got hurt.", "He bit people.", "He ate too much."], "correct_answer": 1, "correct_answer_json": null, "parent_question_id": "cap-114-english-reading-passage-20", "media": null, "source": "official", "source_meta": {"parser_version": "cap_v0.1", "merger_version": "cap_merger_v0.2", "parsed_at": "2026-04-25T18:39:39+00:00", "source_pdf_sha1": "dec9486b85ec", "answer_pdf_sha1": "6a98d676c5b0", "flags": [], "parse_confidence": 1.0, "original_question_number": 20, "raw_text": "20. What happened to Rex?\n    (A) He got lost.\n    (B) He got hurt.\n    (C) He bit people.\n    (D) He ate too much.\n", "explanation_source": "ai_v1_inline"}, "is_active": true, "auto_gradable": true, "difficulty": 3, "explanation": "原文「He was hit by a car last night」直接說明 Rex 受傷，故 (B) He got hurt 正確。(A) 沒有走失；(C) 沒咬人；(D) 沒提吃太多。"}, {"id": "cap-114-english-reading-021", "exam_id": "cap", "subject_id": "sub-cap-english-reading", "paper_id": "cap-114-english-reading", "question_type": "single_choice", "question_text": "How did the writer help Rex?", "options": ["By calling the police.", "By making him exercise.", "By taking him to see a doctor.", "By looking for a new home for him."], "correct_answer": 1, "correct_answer_json": null, "parent_question_id": "cap-114-english-reading-passage-20", "media": null, "source": "official", "source_meta": {"parser_version": "cap_v0.1", "merger_version": "cap_merger_v0.2", "parsed_at": "2026-04-25T18:39:39+00:00", "source_pdf_sha1": "dec9486b85ec", "answer_pdf_sha1": "6a98d676c5b0", "flags": [], "parse_confidence": 1.0, "original_question_number": 21, "raw_text": "21.     How did the writer help Rex?\n        (A) By calling the police.\n        (B) By making him exercise.\n        (C) By taking him to see a doctor.\n        (D) By looking for a new home for him.\n\n\n\n\n", "explanation_source": "ai_v1_inline"}, "is_active": true, "auto_gradable": true, "difficulty": 3, "explanation": "原文「we decided to take him for a walk every evening. Because of the exercise, Rex became healthier and stronger」直接呼應 (B) By making him exercise，故 (B) 正確。(A)(C)(D) 文中皆未對應。"}, {"id": "cap-114-english-reading-022", "exam_id": "cap", "subject_id": "sub-cap-english-reading", "paper_id": "cap-114-english-reading", "question_type": "single_choice", "question_text": "What do we know about Mark from the dialogue?", "options": ["He made Linda unhappy.", "He is looking for a new job.", "He did not like Linda’s cake.", "He is getting married to Jenny."], "correct_answer": 0, "correct_answer_json": null, "parent_question_id": "cap-114-english-reading-passage-22", "media": null, "source": "official", "source_meta": {"parser_version": "cap_v0.1", "merger_version": "cap_merger_v0.2", "parsed_at": "2026-04-25T18:39:39+00:00", "source_pdf_sha1": "dec9486b85ec", "answer_pdf_sha1": "6a98d676c5b0", "flags": [], "parse_confidence": 1.0, "original_question_number": 22, "raw_text": "22. What do we know about Mark from the dialogue?\n    (A) He made Linda unhappy.\n    (B) He is looking for a new job.\n    (C) He did not like Linda’s cake.\n    (D) He is getting married to Jenny.\n", "explanation_source": "ai_v1_inline"}, "is_active": true, "auto_gradable": true, "difficulty": 3, "explanation": "本題搭配對話內容（pdftotext 未抽到完整對話）。從選項配置與答案 (A) He made Linda unhappy 推測，對話應呈現 Mark 做了某件事讓 Linda 不快的情境，故 (A) 正確。其餘選項屬無關訊息。"}, {"id": "cap-114-english-reading-023", "exam_id": "cap", "subject_id": "sub-cap-english-reading", "paper_id": "cap-114-english-reading", "question_type": "single_choice", "question_text": "Which is most likely an example of stealing someone＇     s thunder?           likely 可能", "options": ["Dennis never changes his mind except when his wife tells him to.", "Melisa tells Tom she’ll go to the party but tells her mom she’ll stay home.", "Jeff tells everyone he’ll move abroad when Ivy is still telling them about her baby.", "\u0007Alisa says she doesn’t care what we have for lunch but also doesn’t like the restaurant we chose."], "correct_answer": 2, "correct_answer_json": null, "parent_question_id": "cap-114-english-reading-passage-22", "media": null, "source": "official", "source_meta": {"parser_version": "cap_v0.1", "merger_version": "cap_merger_v0.2", "parsed_at": "2026-04-25T18:39:39+00:00", "source_pdf_sha1": "dec9486b85ec", "answer_pdf_sha1": "6a98d676c5b0", "flags": [], "parse_confidence": 1.0, "original_question_number": 23, "raw_text": "23. Which is most likely an example of stealing someone＇     s thunder?           likely 可能\n    (A) Dennis never changes his mind except when his wife tells him to.\n    (B) Melisa tells Tom she’ll go to the party but tells her mom she’ll stay home.\n    (C) Jeff tells everyone he’ll move abroad when Ivy is still telling them about her baby.\n    (D) \u0007Alisa says she doesn’t care what we have for lunch but also doesn’t like the restaurant\n        we chose.\n\n", "explanation_source": "ai_v1_inline"}, "is_active": true, "auto_gradable": true, "difficulty": 3, "explanation": "「stealing someone''s thunder」意為在他人正受關注時搶走鋒頭。(C) Jeff 在 Ivy 還在分享自己孩子消息時宣布「我要搬到國外」，搶走 Ivy 的關注焦點，最符合此習語，故 (C) 正確。(A) 是聽從妻子；(B) 是說謊；(D) 是被動接受。"}, {"id": "cap-114-english-reading-024", "exam_id": "cap", "subject_id": "sub-cap-english-reading", "paper_id": "cap-114-english-reading", "question_type": "single_choice", "question_text": "What can you do with a White Lake City Card?", "options": ["Save 20% on children’s train tickets.", "Visit any public museum in the city for free.", "Take a train to places out of the three zones.", "Move around the city by metro as much as you want."], "correct_answer": 3, "correct_answer_json": null, "parent_question_id": "cap-114-english-reading-passage-24", "media": null, "source": "official", "source_meta": {"parser_version": "cap_v0.1", "merger_version": "cap_merger_v0.2", "parsed_at": "2026-04-25T18:39:39+00:00", "source_pdf_sha1": "dec9486b85ec", "answer_pdf_sha1": "6a98d676c5b0", "flags": [], "parse_confidence": 1.0, "original_question_number": 24, "raw_text": "24. What can you do with a White Lake City Card?\n    (A) Save 20% on children’s train tickets.   \n    (B) Visit any public museum in the city for free.  \n    (C) Take a train to places out of the three zones.  \n    (D) Move around the city by metro as much as you want.  \n", "explanation_source": "ai_v1_inline"}, "is_active": true, "auto_gradable": true, "difficulty": 3, "explanation": "原文「visit the city by metro, bus, or train as many times as you want」明白指可無限搭乘公共運輸，故 (D) Move around the city by metro as much as you want 正確。(A) 八折是博物館門票而非兒童火車；(B) 博物館是 20% 折扣不是免費；(C) 卡只能在三個 zone 內使用。"}, {"id": "cap-114-english-reading-025", "exam_id": "cap", "subject_id": "sub-cap-english-reading", "paper_id": "cap-114-english-reading", "question_type": "single_choice", "question_text": "Stacy is going to White Lake City and is staying at a hotel near the White Lake Main\nStation.  She wants to visit the Museum of White Lake City History on Friday and see\nWhite Lake on Saturday.  If she plans to buy (a) White Lake City Card(s), which of the four\nchoices will be best for her and cost her the least?", "options": ["A 3-day Card for Zone 1.", "A Weekend Card for Zones 1-3.", "A 1-day Card for Zone 1 and a Weekend Card for Zones 1-2.", "A 1-day Card for Zones 1-2 and a Weekend Card for Zones 1-2."], "correct_answer": 2, "correct_answer_json": null, "parent_question_id": "cap-114-english-reading-passage-24", "media": null, "source": "official", "source_meta": {"parser_version": "cap_v0.1", "merger_version": "cap_merger_v0.2", "parsed_at": "2026-04-25T18:39:39+00:00", "source_pdf_sha1": "dec9486b85ec", "answer_pdf_sha1": "6a98d676c5b0", "flags": [], "parse_confidence": 1.0, "original_question_number": 25, "raw_text": "25. Stacy is going to White Lake City and is staying at a hotel near the White Lake Main\n    Station.  She wants to visit the Museum of White Lake City History on Friday and see\n    White Lake on Saturday.  If she plans to buy (a) White Lake City Card(s), which of the four\n    choices will be best for her and cost her the least?\n    (A) A 3-day Card for Zone 1.\n    (B) A Weekend Card for Zones 1-3.\n    (C) A 1-day Card for Zone 1 and a Weekend Card for Zones 1-2.\n    (D) A 1-day Card for Zones 1-2 and a Weekend Card for Zones 1-2.\n", "explanation_source": "ai_v1_inline"}, "is_active": true, "auto_gradable": true, "difficulty": 3, "explanation": "Stacy 週五要去歷史博物館（Zone 1，主車站附近）+ 週六去 White Lake（在 Zones 1-2）。週五用 1-day for Zone 1（$20）+ 週末用 Weekend Card for Zones 1-2（$50）= $70 是涵蓋目的地的最便宜組合，故 (C) 正確。(A) 3-day Zone 1 不含週六也不含 White Lake；(B) Weekend 1-3 不含週五；(D) 1-day Zones 1-2 多花錢且 Friday 只需 Zone 1。"}, {"id": "cap-114-english-reading-026", "exam_id": "cap", "subject_id": "sub-cap-english-reading", "paper_id": "cap-114-english-reading", "question_type": "single_choice", "question_text": "What is Rolling Acres?", "options": ["A zoo.", "A campground.", "A vacation farm.", "A family restaurant."], "correct_answer": 2, "correct_answer_json": null, "parent_question_id": "cap-114-english-reading-passage-26", "media": null, "source": "official", "source_meta": {"parser_version": "cap_v0.1", "merger_version": "cap_merger_v0.2", "parsed_at": "2026-04-25T18:39:39+00:00", "source_pdf_sha1": "dec9486b85ec", "answer_pdf_sha1": "6a98d676c5b0", "flags": [], "parse_confidence": 1.0, "original_question_number": 26, "raw_text": "26. What is Rolling Acres?\n    (A) A zoo.\n    (B) A campground.\n    (C) A vacation farm.\n    (D) A family restaurant.\n", "explanation_source": "ai_v1_inline"}, "is_active": true, "auto_gradable": true, "difficulty": 3, "explanation": "原文「Rolling Acres used to be just a sheep farm, but now…it has become a popular place for families to go on vacation」直接點出是供家庭度假的農場，故 (C) A vacation farm 正確。(A) 不是動物園；(B) 不是露營場；(D) 不是餐廳。"}, {"id": "cap-114-english-reading-027", "exam_id": "cap", "subject_id": "sub-cap-english-reading", "paper_id": "cap-114-english-reading", "question_type": "single_choice", "question_text": "What do we learn from the first paragraph?                             paragraph 段落", "options": ["What Libby does at Rolling Acres.", "What visitors think of Rolling Acres.", "Why Libby’s grandparents started Rolling Acres.", "What the Larson family’s plans are for Rolling Acres."], "correct_answer": 0, "correct_answer_json": null, "parent_question_id": "cap-114-english-reading-passage-26", "media": null, "source": "official", "source_meta": {"parser_version": "cap_v0.1", "merger_version": "cap_merger_v0.2", "parsed_at": "2026-04-25T18:39:39+00:00", "source_pdf_sha1": "dec9486b85ec", "answer_pdf_sha1": "6a98d676c5b0", "flags": [], "parse_confidence": 1.0, "original_question_number": 27, "raw_text": "27. What do we learn from the first paragraph?                             paragraph 段落\n    (A) What Libby does at Rolling Acres.\n    (B) What visitors think of Rolling Acres.\n    (C) Why Libby’s grandparents started Rolling Acres.\n    (D) What the Larson family’s plans are for Rolling Acres.\n", "explanation_source": "ai_v1_inline"}, "is_active": true, "auto_gradable": true, "difficulty": 3, "explanation": "第一段描述 Libby 早起、拖地、收信件、迎接遊客等工作內容，主軸即「Libby 在 Rolling Acres 做什麼」，故 (A) 正確。(B) 文中未呈現訪客觀感；(C) 祖父母創立原因僅一句帶過；(D) 未談未來計畫。"}, {"id": "cap-114-english-reading-028", "exam_id": "cap", "subject_id": "sub-cap-english-reading", "paper_id": "cap-114-english-reading", "question_type": "single_choice", "question_text": "What does making sacrifices mean?", "options": ["Learning to make money and use it wisely.", "Getting to know different sides of your family.", "Making excuses for failing to do something difficult.", "Giving up something important to do something else."], "correct_answer": 3, "correct_answer_json": null, "parent_question_id": "cap-114-english-reading-passage-26", "media": null, "source": "official", "source_meta": {"parser_version": "cap_v0.1", "merger_version": "cap_merger_v0.2", "parsed_at": "2026-04-25T18:39:39+00:00", "source_pdf_sha1": "dec9486b85ec", "answer_pdf_sha1": "6a98d676c5b0", "flags": [], "parse_confidence": 1.0, "original_question_number": 28, "raw_text": "28. What does making sacrifices mean?\n    (A) Learning to make money and use it wisely.\n    (B) Getting to know different sides of your family.\n    (C) Making excuses for failing to do something difficult.\n    (D) Giving up something important to do something else.\n\n\n\n\n", "explanation_source": "ai_v1_inline"}, "is_active": true, "auto_gradable": true, "difficulty": 3, "explanation": "Libby 引文「I''d love to sleep until noon or go to summer camp like other kids…My friends stopped inviting me on trips」清楚說明她為了家業放棄了想做的事，故 (D) Giving up something important to do something else 正確。(A) 只談賺錢；(B) 認識家人非主旨；(C) 找藉口與 sacrifice 反向。"}]'::jsonb) AS t(
